summary: This is a forensic imaging log from a Tableau TD2 device, documenting the creation of a disk image from a Seagate hard drive (serial Z6E8K1EV) as part of the Epstein investigation. The log confirms successful imaging with verification hashes matching, indicating the evidence was properly preserved.

events.title: Forensic imaging of hard drive
events.description: A Seagate hard drive (model ST500DM002-1BD142, serial Z6E8K1EV) was imaged using a Tableau TD2 forensic duplicator at the TD2 CRYSTAL CITY 2 location. The imaging process created 227 files totaling approximately 500.1 GB of data with zero errors and matching source/verification hashes.

keyFacts: A 500.1 GB Seagate hard drive (serial Z6E8K1EV) was forensically imaged on August 11, 2019 as part of the Epstein investigation.
The imaging was performed using a Tableau TD2 forensic duplicator at location 'TD2 CRYSTAL CITY 2'.
The process created 227 image files with matching SHA1 and MD5 hashes (SHA1: be9791bce5978ccdf3111a54eac84606739c0424, MD5: 48f956e5ddab702d48177534ec96d026), confirming data integrity.
The hard drive had firmware dated May 02, 2013 21:35:47, suggesting the drive was from around that time period.
The imaging was logged with Case ID 'Epstein case # pending', indicating this was part of the ongoing investigation.
